Business Brief -- Ryder System Inc.:
   Report of Quarterly Loss
   Tied to Charge Is Expected
Ryder added that it is comfortable with Wall Street
estimates that the company will report earnings from
continuing operations of about 28 cents a share in the fourth
quarter.
   In the 1990 fourth quarter, Ryder reported a loss of $25
million, or 38 cents a share, that included a charge for
discontinuing the aircraft leasing business. For all of 1990,
the company reported earnings of $42.7 million, or 43 cents a
share.
   In late New York Stock Exchange trading, Ryder stock was
quoted at $23.50 a share, up $1.75.